# ── Template .privacy manifest ────────────────────────────────────
# Each non-comment line is a single env-var NAME that your task needs.
# The runner resolves values from configs/privacy.local.env at runtime
# and injects them into the executor container as environment variables.
#
# Task prompts should refer to credentials by env-var name, e.g.:
#
#     Use the token in $API_TOKEN against $API_BASE.
#
# Leave this file empty (or delete it) if your task needs no
# credentials at all. The lines below match the placeholder keys in
# configs/privacy.example.env so `load_task` can demo the full
# injection path end-to-end.
API_TOKEN
API_BASE
